# Cursor rules — NIS / PLOS Monorepo

Cursor reads this file at the start of every chat. These are the same rules as `CLAUDE.md` — keep them in sync if you edit either.

**Both AIs share PLOS work now** (Claude Code led the May 2026 visual redesign of `plos-frontend`; Cursor continues backend work and shares the frontend). See ownership table + coordination protocol below.

**Before starting any task, read `BACKLOG.md` at the repo root** — it's the single source of truth for pending work and ownership.

**Last updated:** 2026-05-23

## What's in this repo

Monorepo holding two products under one brand (NIS):
- `apps/web/` → NIS brand site (Next.js, thenispace.com) — **Claude Code primary. Cursor: hands off unless BACKLOG.md tags an item `cursor` or `either`.**
- `plos-backend/` → PLOS API (NestJS) — **Cursor primary. Claude Code touches only when an item is tagged for them.**
- `plos-frontend/` → PLOS web app (Vite + Mantine) — **Shared. Coordinate via BACKLOG.md.**
- `packages/brand-tokens/` → shared design tokens — **Nikita owns. Don't change values without explicit approval.**
- `packages/ui/` → shared UI primitives — either AI may add components with PR review
- `packages/razorpay-sdk/` → shared Razorpay client — either AI may extend with PR review
- `docs/` → product context and roadmaps
- `BACKLOG.md` → pending work register (READ FIRST)
- `START_HERE.md` → current state + what's running + click-through flow

## Coordination protocol (shared frontend)

The protocol is simple: **`BACKLOG.md` is the queue.** Don't start a task that isn't in there or isn't tagged for you.

1. Open `BACKLOG.md`, find an item tagged `cursor` or `either`. To pick up something tagged `claude`, ask the human first.
2. Edit the line to `[in progress · YYYY-MM-DD · cursor]` and commit before writing code — this is the lock.
3. Branch as `feat/plos-<short-name>`. One PR per item.
4. When done, strike through the bullet, add `→ shipped in <commit-or-PR>`. Update `START_HERE.md` if user-visible.
5. New pending work discovered mid-task → add a bullet with priority + owner. Don't leave silent TODOs in code.

If you need to touch a file outside your primary area without a BACKLOG.md entry, write the entry FIRST, get human approval, then code.

## Read before substantial work

Plans live in `/Volumes/DevSSD/dev/claude/`:
- `plos_code_plan_v1.md` — your engineering plan (sprints I → P)
- `plos_plan_review_v1.md` — strategy decisions and the revised roadmap
- `nis_code_plan_v1.md` — context on what Claude Code is doing in `apps/web/`

## Cross-app rules

1. `plos-backend` and `plos-frontend` may NOT import from `apps/web/`. Communication is HTTP-only.
2. `apps/web/` may NOT import from `plos-backend/` or `plos-frontend/`. Same reason.
3. Always import brand from `@nis/brand-tokens`. Never hardcode colors, fonts, spacing.
4. Use `@nis/ui` Button/Card/Badge primitives instead of raw HTML buttons (when they exist — see BACKLOG.md P1).
5. Use `@nis/razorpay-sdk` for any Razorpay calls — never instantiate the SDK directly.

## Coding conventions

- TypeScript everywhere. No `any` without a comment.
- No `console.log` in committed code. Use Pino in backend; dev-only console with eslint-disable in frontend.
- Use `Intl.NumberFormat` for currency, never hardcode `₹`.
- Store dates UTC, display in user's timezone from settings.
- Test critical paths (money handling, auth, scheduler).

## Frontend conventions (when working in plos-frontend/)

Claude Code's May 2026 redesign established these patterns — preserve them:
- **Shared design components** live in `src/components/plos/` — `PlosModuleHero`, `PlosReveal`, `PlosTilt`, `ModuleScenes`, `Charts`, `ResponsibilityRow`, `PlosCategoryModule`, `TodayPulse`, `LifeRings`, `PlosMarquee`. Reuse them; don't create parallel versions.
- **Glass / streak chain CSS** lives in `src/styles/plos-prototype/*.css` (copied from prototype, treat as read-only) plus `src/styles/plos-mobile.css` (our responsive layer — edit here).
- **Mobile responsive** — sidebar collapses to a Drawer at ≤900px (`useMediaQuery('(max-width: 900px)')` in `AppLayout`); a hamburger button in `PlosTopbar` opens it. KPI grid drops to 1-col at ≤640px.
- **Auth + queries** — `useAppSelector(s => s.auth.user)` for the current user; `@tanstack/react-query` for all server data; `responsibilityService`, `personService`, etc. in `src/services/`.
- **Brand tokens** — colors from `var(--plos-accent)` etc. (defined in `tokens.css`); fonts via `var(--nis-font-display)` (Sora) / `var(--nis-font-serif)` (Instrument Serif italic).

## Git workflow

- Branch naming: `feat/plos-<short-name>`, `feat/web-<short-name>`, `pkg/<package>-<change>`.
- No direct commits to `main`. Always PR.
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`.
- One PR = one BACKLOG.md item.

## Specifically NOT to do

- Don't switch payment processor from Razorpay.
- Don't move shop to Shopify.
- Don't build "for everyone" — PLOS wedge is Indian freelancers + dual-income households.
- Don't gate free-tier features without checking the pricing plan.
- Don't send notifications without opt-in checks.
- Don't store secrets in code — use `.env` files.
- Don't restructure `plos-frontend/src/components/plos/` or `src/styles/plos-prototype/` without an entry in BACKLOG.md — that's the design-system surface both AIs depend on.

## When in doubt

- Item not in `BACKLOG.md`? Don't code it. Add the entry first.
- Touching `packages/*`? Open a PR with a clear "why" in the description. Ishank reviews shared packages.
- Touching `apps/web/`? Don't, unless the BACKLOG.md item is tagged for you.
- Unsure which doc to read? Start with `BACKLOG.md`, then `START_HERE.md`, then `SETUP.md`.
